cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IT 

The paper deals with the problem of releasing statistical queries while preserving differential privacy, which is a topic in the intersection of computer security (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). The focus on sparse queries suggests that the paper may be more relevant to data structures and databases, but the use of differential privacy and the accuracy bounds make it relevant to the other sub-categories as well.
